<p>To specify a prior distribution over 
 <inline-formula>
  <inline-graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1000520.e108.jpg" mimetype="image" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
 </inline-formula>, we assume that each indicator acts 
 <italic>a priori</italic> as an independent Bernoulli random variable (RV) with small success probability 
 <inline-formula>
  <inline-graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1000520.e109.jpg" mimetype="image" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
 </inline-formula>. The sum of independent Bernoulli RVs yields a Binomial distribution over their sum 
 <inline-formula>
  <inline-graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1000520.e110.jpg" mimetype="image" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
 </inline-formula>. In the limit that 
 <inline-formula>
  <inline-graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1000520.e111.jpg" mimetype="image" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
 </inline-formula>, this prior conveniently collapses to
 <disp-formula>
  <graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1000520.e112.jpg" mimetype="image" position="float" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  <label>(4)</label>
 </disp-formula>where 
 <inline-formula>
  <inline-graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1000520.e113.jpg" mimetype="image" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
 </inline-formula> is the prior expected number of edges in graph 
 <inline-formula>
  <inline-graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1000520.e114.jpg" mimetype="image" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
 </inline-formula>.
</p>
